White hanes at 1, nd when black cuts with 2, white plays dansu at 3, leaving black with a weak group to deal with. Then, after black defends with 4, white 5 captures the black stone on the lower side.

Black defends his territory on the right with 6 without too much complaint.

The result is neck and neck. It iss hard to tell who's better.

